At least 600 homeless families have started rebuilding their homes following shack fires over the Easter weekend.The Cape Town fire and rescue service responded to 10 major fire incidents since the start of the Easter holiday period.Separate fires occurred in Hout Bay and Gugulethu, where two people died. In Hout Bay, one person died when a fire tore through Imizamo Yethu on Sunday.Last month, in the same informal settlement, fire broke out killing four people and destroying hundreds of homes.The South African Red Cross Society assisted affected families with humanitarian relief, hot meals, blankets, vanity packs and clothing.Officials said it is still unclear what sparked the fires.-TNA Reporter 